    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'd imagine it would be nicer to take an opportunity and redesign the `nvim_buf_del()` to be more straightforward and maybe more useful than `nvim_buf_delete()`. For example:\r\n\r\n- Taking into account [this comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/33330#issuecomment-2781440361), it might be a good idea to redesign actions and parametrization. Some ideas:\r\n    - Make `nvim_buf_del(buf, {})` equivalent to `:bdelete`. This default action is less confusing naming-wise, but I would say that using `:bwipeout` is more common in plugins than `:bdelete`.\r\n    - The equivalent of `:bwipeout` can be `nvim_buf_del(buf, { wipeout = true })`.\r\n    - OR make it possible to replace both `:bwipeout` and `:bunload`. It can be something like `nvim_buf_del(buf, { type = \"delete\"|\"wipeout\"|\"unload\" })`. Maybe also add `\"unlist\"` to possible values of `action`, although it seems to be the same as `nvim_set_option_value('buflisted', false, { buf = buf })`.\r\n    - Preserving `opts.force` from `nvim_buf_delete` is a good idea and acts like `!` for respective commands.\r\n- Take #33351 into account and add `preserve_layout` boolean flag to options. This is not necessary for the initial PR.",
